M. Bussereau recalled that "the lowering of taxes on employers in the amount of 100 million euros" was the subject of an amendment by the government to the 2009 bill of corrected finances, which was passed by the National Assembly on the night of Thursday to Friday.
The government demands "an identical" vote from the Senate.
The signature of the TLF allows the agreement to apply first to the companies affiliated to the organisation and then to apply to the entire profession in the event of an extension by the Minister of Labour.
This will be the case "in the shortest time", Bussereau assures.
The opposition of employers' associations can only delay the proceedings.
FNTR denounced a "frauding trade" because the EUR 100 million "had already been promised to the sector to compensate for part of the carbon tax".
The Secretary of State for Transport forced us to negotiate as soon as possible, but not on the basis of a joint analysis, but in order not to push the goose eaters away on the approaching Christmas days, the Unostra laments.
For the Otre Association, the agreement threatens "to dig a large grave for the small and medium-sized enterprises of the industry in the next 12 months".
