In these days of storms and accidents not only car repairers earn
Every day thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are towed to the workshops, where an expert must assess the damage and the cost of the repair.
Not a single accident is the same and calculating the cost of parts and working hours can be a lengthy and complicated task.
The calculation of repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including parts and working hours, can take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest informatics tools, it is a matter of minutes
This is why almost 100% of the evaluators use these types of systems.
The service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs shall collect the information they receive from manufacturers in order to process it afterwards and to offer it to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American Solera group, is the market leader; 80% of all reports are produced with their products.
The other two companies competing with the tool market for review and preparation of a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data that manufacturers provide is anything but easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers are working together, each of them providing the information in a different format.
Furthermore, the amount of data to be processed is increasing, up to the point that more versions, variants and motorizations have been introduced in the last five years than in the entire fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car enters the market, the work begins for the companies.
It is a laborious task, because every single one of the thousands of vehicle parts must be catagolized and its price entered.
In addition, an "intelligent" graphic image is created by each model, on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much-sold model, the work can be completed in one week if the process is progressing rapidly.
If this is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. At present, Audatex has full information for 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the vehicle park on the roads, it is more than 99%.
In order to carry out documentation work and to produce databases, Audatex has eight centres distributed around the world (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specialises in specific brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics professionals) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests EUR 90 million a year in the development of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers receive updates every other day.
The development of this enormous flow of information enables companies to use it in different ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but depending on the country there are also tools for managing scrap parts or for calculating the value of a car.
The only company that informs about a leader about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer this offer in Spain, but in the United States.
When reviewing the products Audatex offers, it is easy to get an overview of the type of support it provides to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, with the star of the AudaPlus products being a standard solution for assessing accidents for the evaluators.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles as well as light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it contains the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the painting prices.
This tool is paid according to the intended use, i.e. for each report.
Most expensive it will be for customers who rarely use it up to ten times a month, namely 5.75 euros per month.
On the other hand, each insurance company that makes thousands of reports negotiates the price with Audatex.
With other products, such as AudaVIN, one can completely identify a vehicle and the equipment with which it ran from the assembly line, solely on the basis of the chassis number.
AudaGlass deals with the vehicle discs, and AudaSubastas is an open service for the specialist market on the Internet, which can be offered for vehicles that have been declared to be total damage.
Your statistical service is very useful in identifying trends, conducting geodemographic analyses or in order to obtain information on the deviations by brand and model.
For example, one can examine how many models of a particular car brand had to go to the workshop due to breakdowns or how many of them were involved in a serious accident during a certain period of time.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of computer tools.
